# Boot Script

A **boot script** is a single piece of JavaScript that TWikki runs **before anything else** — even before `tw.storage` exists. It is the earliest customization hook in the boot process.

The platform looks for the source under the `localStorage` key `/twikki.boot.js`. If it finds it, it `eval`s the source (which must evaluate to a function), calls that function with `tw`, and awaits it if it returns a promise — all before the default storage backing is set up.

```js
// /twikki.boot.js — source must evaluate to a function
(function (tw) {
  // runs before tw.storage is initialised; mutate tw here
});
```

Because it runs so early, the most common use is to **replace the storage backend** — for example to route `tw.store` through IndexedDB instead of `localStorage`.

**Failure-safe.** If the script fails to parse, throws, or rejects, the platform alerts once and continues with the default `localStorage` backing. A broken boot script can never brick the app.

**Scope.** The boot script lives in `localStorage` and is global per origin — installing one affects **every** workspace on the device, not just the current one.

The base [[IndexedDBStoragePlugin]] is a real, installable example: it writes a boot script that swaps `tw.storage` for an IndexedDB-backed wrapper.

See [Boot Script Docs](https://github.com/cawoodm/twikki/blob/main/docs/BootScript.md) for the full contract and a worked IndexedDB example, and [[Concepts]] / the [Boot order docs](https://github.com/cawoodm/twikki/blob/main/docs/BOOT.md) for where it fits in the wider boot sequence.

TWikki's event bus lets you trigger any action from a link. The URL format is `#msg:<event>:<params>`.

## Examples

| What you want | Link | Raw syntax |
|---------------|------|------------|
| Open a specific tiddler | [Show Welcome](#msg:tiddler.show:Welcome) | `#msg:tiddler.show:Welcome` |
| Create a new tiddler | [New tiddler](#msg:tiddler.new) | `#msg:tiddler.new` |
| Search for a term | [Search "events"](#msg:search:events) | `#msg:search:events` |
| Open all tiddlers tagged Help | [Open all Help](#msg:ui.open.all:tag:Help) | `#msg:ui.open.all:tag:Help` |
| Close all open tiddlers | [Close all](#msg:ui.close.all) | `#msg:ui.close.all` |
| Save to localStorage | [Save now](#msg:save) | `#msg:save` |
| Switch workspace | [Go to default](#msg:workspace.load:default) | `#msg:workspace.load:default` |

## Using events in tiddler content

Anywhere you write markdown you can embed a `msg:` link:

```
[Open my note](#msg:tiddler.show:My%20Note)
[New tiddler](#msg:tiddler.new)
[Search events](#msg:search:events)
```

Spaces in params must be percent-encoded (`My%20Note`) or wrapped in quotes (`"My Note"`).

## Calling events from plugins

```js
// Subscribe (listen)
tw.events.subscribe('tiddler.created', title => {
  console.log('Created:', title);
}, 'MyPlugin.onCreate');

// Send (broadcast)
tw.events.send('tiddler.show', 'Welcome');

// Override (replace existing handler)
tw.events.override('markdown.render', text => myRenderer.render(text));

// Filter (transform a value through a chain)
tw.events.subscribe('renderer.pre', (text, {tiddler}) => {
  return text.replace(/TODO:.*/g, '');
}, 'MyPlugin.stripTodos');
```

See the [full events reference](https://github.com/cawoodm/twikki/blob/main/docs/EVENTS.md) for all available events.

This plugin provides some examples of a macro with custom styling.

Feel free to look at the [code](#ExamplePlugin::Code).

# Examples

## Greet John Smith

`<<example.hello "John Smith">>`: <<example.hello "John Smith">>

# Meta

<<pluginMeta ExamplePlugin>>

# Data

```json
[
  {"code": "de", "language": "German"},
  {"code": "en", "language": "English"}
]
```

# Code

```javascript
(function () {
  return {
    meta: {
      name: 'ExamplePlugin',
      version: '1.0.1',
      platform: '0.27.0',
      author: 'Marc Cawood',
      description: 'Demo plugin: shows the {meta, init, start} contract by registering a macro.',
      url: 'https://cawoodm.github.io/twikki',
    },
    init() {
      // Register a macro at init time, after all plugins are loaded.
      tw.extensions.registerMacro(
        'example',
        'hello',
        name => {
          return `<span class=example>Hello ${name}</span>`;
        },
        {
          description: 'Demo macro: greets the named person.',
          example: '<<example.hello "John Smith">>',
          version: '1.0.0',
        },
      );
    },
    start() {
      // Optional. Empty for this demo — the macro is the only side effect.
    },
  };
})();
```

# StyleSheet

```css
span.example {
  color: red;
}
```

# Tests

